  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Menu Sub-Items Spacing and Sizing Issues\n\nCorrect the visual layout of submenu items to ensure consistent spacing and appropriate sizing throughout the navigation menu.\n\nRequirements:\n- Identify all menu components that display sub-items (dropdowns, nested menus, etc.)\n- Ensure consistent padding and margin between submenu items\n- Set appropriate font size for submenu items (typically slightly smaller than parent menu items)\n- Verify proper vertical spacing between individual submenu entries\n- Check horizontal indentation for nested submenu levels\n- Ensure submenu container has appropriate width and doesn't clip content\n- Test across different viewport sizes for responsive behavior\n- Verify alignment and spacing is consistent with the overall design system\n- Check both hover and active states maintain proper spacing\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Submenu items with varying text lengths\n- Multi-level nested submenus\n- Submenus with icons or additional elements\n- Mobile/touch interfaces where spacing affects usability",
